				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DementedPurple wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And how would I get the other bit? Do you load a memory address and the use &quot;AND other memory location&quot;</div><br />Yes, this. Operations on the 6502 generally use what's in the accumulator as an implicit argument and as the implicit destination. So, for example, AND #$10 will perform a bitwise AND with whatever is in the accumulator and the constant number $10 (that's 10 in hexadecimal, a.k.a. 16 in decimal) and finally put the result in the accumulator. By &quot;bitwise&quot;, I mean the rightmost bit of the accumulator will get AND'd with the rightmost bit of the number $10 to form the rightmost bit of the result.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

